HEADWORD: Subdeacon
<hw>Sub*dea"con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sub-</ets> + <ets>deacon</ets>: cf. L.
<ets>subdiaconus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>One belonging to
an order in the Roman Catholic Church, next interior to the order of
deacons; also, a member of a minor order in the Greek Church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

